<input type="hidden" name="course" value="problemset">
<input type="hidden" name="task" value="1162">
Here are some possible methods using which we can sort the elements of an array in increasing order:<ol>
<li> At each step, choose two adjacent elements and swap them.<br />
<li> At each step, choose any two elements and swap them.<br />
<li> At each step, choose any element and move it to another position.<br />
<li> At each step, choose any element and move it to the front of the array.<br />
</ol>
Given a permutation of numbers $1,2,\ldots,n$, calculate the minimum number of steps to sort the array using the above methods.<br />
<br />
<b id="input">Input</b><br />
<br />
The first input line contains an integer $n$.<br />
<br />
The second line contains $n$ integers describing the permutation.<br />
<br />
<b id="output">Output</b><br />
<br />
Print four numbers: the minimum number of steps using each method.<br />
<br />
<b id="constraints">Constraints</b><br />
<ul>
<li>$1 \le n \le 2 \cdot 10^5$<br />
</ul>
<b id="example">Example</b><br />
<br />
Input:<br />
<code>8<br />
7 8 2 6 5 1 3 4</code><br />
<br />
Output:<br />
<code>20 6 5 6</code>    </div>
